When you use the contract-based REST API, the current date is used as the business date, and the branch that you specified when signing in is used as the current branch. When you create or update a record by using the contract-based REST API, you may need to use other values of the business date or current branch. To do this, you use the custom HTTP headers ''PX-CbApiBusinessDate'' and ''PX-CbApiBranch'' in the HTTP requests you make. See the following sections for details on the URL, headers, HTTP method, body, and response format.[anchor|#_db7ce41e-2c09-4c9d-99dc-dc1987627a5d]((({S:Warn}The new values that you specify for the business date or current branch are valid only for the current HTTP request. ))){br}{TOC} ==URL== When you create or update a record in Acumatica ERP, you use the following URL: {{http://<Base endpoint URL>/<Top-level entity>}}.{br}
The URL has the following components:[anchor|#_5863ce77-8be1-44d6-9342-fb7c2c1b6025] *{{<Base endpoint URL>}} is the URL of the contract-based endpoint through which you are going to work with Acumatica ERP, which has the following format: {{http://<Acumatica ERP instance URL>/entity/<Endpoint name>/<Endpoint version>/}}. *{{<Top-level entity>}} is the name of the entity for which you are going to create or update a record. {br}
For example, suppose that you want to update a stock item record in a local Acumatica ERP instance with the name ''AcumaticaDB'' by using a system endpoint with the name ''Default'' and Version 18.200.001. You would use the following URL to update a record: ''http://localhost/AcumaticaDB/entity/Default/18.200.001/StockItem''. ==Headers== You can use the following optional headers for changing the business date or current branch.[anchor|#_40bf8194-174d-41e1-9ba1-dce56cf597b4] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="25%" ! Header !width="75%" ! Description |- | <tt>PX-CbApiBusinessDate</tt> | Optional. Specifies the new business date. The date can be specified in any format. If you omit this header, the current date is used as the business date. |- | <tt>PX-CbApiBranch</tt> | Optional. Specifies the new current branch. The branch should be specified as a branch name. If you omit this header, the branch that you specified when signing in is used as the current branch. |} ==HTTP Method== You use the {{PUT}} HTTP method to change the business date or the current branch while creating or updating a record. ==Parameters, Body, Response, and Status Codes== For information on the request parameters, request body, possible responses and status codes, see the corresponding sections in [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_REST_Create_Record|Creation of a Record] and [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_REST_Update_Record|Update of a Record]. ==HTTP Example== The following request is an example of creating a new journal transaction with ''SweetLife Store'' set as the new current branch and ''01-Jan-2018'' set as the business date.{br}
[anchor|#_af58c866-cfe3-4d1c-85a3-cb0bfd1c9ef1]((({S:Warn}In the request example below, {{<Acumatica ERP instance URL>}} is the URL of the Acumatica ERP instance (such as ''https://my.acumatica.com/MyInstance''). You can omit the instance name in the URL (such as ''https://my.acumatica.com'') if the instance is installed in the root of the website. ))){br}
{{{{PUT / HTTP/1.1 Host: [&lt;Acumatica ERP instance URL&gt;]/entity/Default/18.200.001/JournalTransaction Accept: application/json Content-Type: application/json PX-CbApiBusinessDate: 2018/01/01 PX-CbApiBranch: SweetLife Store
{"Description": {"value": "Test transaction description"}} }}}}[anchor|#_2cf368bb-af55-4291-867b-b5888aa48eba]((({S:Warn}You can find this example in the [https://github.com/Acumatica/Help-and-Training-Examples|Help-and-Training-Examples] repository on GitHub. )))

When you need to create a record by using the contract-based REST API, you access the needed URL address with the {{PUT}} HTTP method and pass the record representation in JSON format in the request body. See the following sections for details on the URL, parameters, HTTP method, HTTP body, HTTP headers, and response format.{br}{TOC}
==URL ==
If you need to create a record in Acumatica ERP, you use the following URL.{{{{http://&lt;Base endpoint URL&gt;/&lt;Top-level entity&gt;
}}}}
The URL has the following components:[anchor|#_b9b24438-8689-4fe6-b0e2-134f5c59bfe3]
*{{<Base endpoint URL>}} is the URL of the contract-based endpoint through which you are going to work with Acumatica ERP, which has the following format: {{http://<Acumatica ERP instance URL>/entity/<Endpoint name>/<Endpoint version>/}}. 
*{{<Top-level entity>}} is the name of the entity for which you are going to create a record.
{br}

For example, suppose that you want to create a stock item record in a local Acumatica ERP instance with the name ''AcumaticaDB'' by using the system endpoint with the name ''Default'' and Version 18.200.001. You should use the following URL to create a record: {{http://localhost/AcumaticaDB/entity/Default/18.200.001/StockItem}}.
==Parameters==
You can use the following parameters when you retrieve a record from Acumatica ERP:[anchor|#_4d4e3624-889e-4f74-8657-437982295990]
*''$expand'': To specify the linked and detail entities to be expanded
*''$select'': To specify the fields of the entity to be returned
*''$custom'': To specify the fields that are not defined in the contract to be returned
{br}

For detailed descriptions of the parameters, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_REST_Parameters|Parameters for Retrieving Records].
==HTTP Method, HTTP Body==
You use the {{PUT}} HTTP method and pass a record in JSON format in the request body. You can find details on how to represent a record in JSON format in [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_REST_Entity_Representation_in_JSON|Representation of a Record in JSON Format]. See below for an example of a customer record representation in JSON format.{{{{{
  "CustomerID" : {value : "JOHNGOOD"},
  "CustomerName" : {value : "John Good"},
  "CustomerClass" : {value : "DEFAULT"},
  "MainContact" : 
    {
      "Email" : {value : "demo@gmail.com"},
      "Address" : 
        {
          "AddressLine1" : {value : "4030 Lake Washington Blvd NE"},
          "AddressLine2" : {value : "Suite 100"},
          "City" : {value : "Kirkland"},
          "State" : {value : "WA" },
          "PostalCode" : {value : "98033"}
        }      
    }  
}
}}}}
==HTTP Headers==
You can specify the following headers in the request.[anchor|#_40bf8194-174d-41e1-9ba1-dce56cf597b4]
{| class="checklist" | width="100%" 
|- 
!width="25%" ! Header
!width="75%" ! Description
|- 
| <tt>Accept</tt>
| Specifies the format of the response body, which can be one of the following:[anchor|#_f83ea400-2a04-4b41-a10a-503c0a1e4d35]
*<tt>application/json</tt>
* <tt>text/json</tt>

|- 
|  <tt>Content-Type</tt>
| Specifies the format of the request body, which can be one of the following:[anchor|#_428be305-088a-4941-91fe-3e3183134561]
*<tt>application/json</tt>
* <tt>text/json</tt>

|- 
|  <tt>If-None-Match</tt>
| Changes the behavior of the {{PUT}} request, which normally either creates a new record or updates an existing one. If you only want to create a new record, use the optional <tt>If-None-Match</tt> header with the {{*}} (asterisk) value.
|}
==Response==
The response of a successful method call contains the created record in JSON format in the response body. The response includes only the values of the fields of the created record that were specified during creation of the record or that were specified to be returned by using the parameters of the request.
==Status Codes==
The following table lists the HTTP status codes that the system returns for a request that creates a record.[anchor|#_de5aba0d-08ea-4e7e-aa2b-1c4e8e0adb19]
{| class="checklist" | width="100%" 
|- 
!width="20%" ! Code
!width="80%" ! Description
|- 
| ''200''
| The request has been completed successfully. The response body contains the created record.
|- 
| ''400''
| [anchor|#_ae0feb62-490e-472f-a179-af71675c0895]
The data specified in the request is invalid.
|- 
| ''401''
| [anchor|#_e115eb28-400c-471f-a6f8-7ebf9f81b4ba]
The user is not signed in to the system.
|- 
| ''403''
| [anchor|#_1988d14f-8aae-437c-8271-d5f75c2e7270]
The user has insufficient rights to access the Acumatica ERP form that corresponds to the entity.
|- 
| ''412''
| You have used the <tt>If-None-Match</tt> header with the {{*}} value, and the record already exists.
|- 
| ''429''
| [anchor|#_d9cb45a7-d9d8-4f3b-b4ce-6026b021fc90]
The number of requests has exceeded the limit imposed by the license (see [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_License_Restrictions_API_Users|License Restrictions for API Users]).
|- 
| ''500''
| [anchor|#_bc869da9-4c1c-466e-acdb-ed9958b081d8]
An internal server error has occurred.
|}
