When you need to update an existing record by using the contract-based REST API, you access the needed URL with the {{PUT}} HTTP method and pass the record representation in JSON format in the request body. See the following sections for details on the URL, parameters, HTTP method, HTTP body, HTTP headers, and response format.{br}{TOC}
==URL==
If you need to update a record in Acumatica ERP, you use the following URL.{{{{http://&lt;Base endpoint URL&gt;/&lt;Top-level entity&gt;
}}}}{br}

The URL has the following components:[anchor|#_5863ce77-8be1-44d6-9342-fb7c2c1b6025]
*{{<Base endpoint URL>}} is the URL of the contract-based endpoint through which you are going to work with Acumatica ERP, which has the following format: {{http://<Acumatica ERP instance URL>/entity/<Endpoint name>/<Endpoint version>/}}. 
*{{<Top-level entity>}} is the name of the entity for which you are going to update a record.
{br}

For example, suppose that you want to update a stock item record in a local Acumatica ERP instance with the name ''AcumaticaDB'' by using the system endpoint with the name ''Default'' and Version 18.200.001. You would use the following URL to update a record: {{http://localhost/AcumaticaDB/entity/Default/18.200.001/StockItem}}.[anchor|#_0aabf54c-3ee5-4703-9d80-711dbdd90909]
==Parameters==
You can use the following parameters when you are updating a record in Acumatica ERP:[anchor|#_33d0cea7-56e5-4c7e-a498-0b739b0429ed]
*''$filter'': To specify filtering conditions that identify the record to be updated
*''$expand'': To specify the linked and detail entities to be expanded
*''$select'': To specify the fields of the entity to be returned
*''$custom'': To specify the fields that are not defined in the contract to be returned
{br}

For detailed descriptions of the parameters, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_REST_Parameters|Parameters for Retrieving Records].
==HTTP Method, HTTP Body==
You use the {{PUT}} HTTP method and pass a record in JSON format in the request body. You can find details on how to represent a record in JSON format in [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_REST_Entity_Representation_in_JSON|Representation of a Record in JSON Format]. {br}

To make it possible for the record to be found by Acumatica ERP, you can use any of the following approaches:[anchor|#_8887242b-00d3-4bcf-a30d-f13dd7de374d]
*Specify the values of the key fields in the record representation in JSON format.
*Specify the value of the <tt>ID</tt> property in the record representation in JSON format.
*Specify the filtering conditions that identify the record in the ''$filter'' parameter of the method. For details on the parameter, see the [[#_0aabf54c-3ee5-4703-9d80-711dbdd90909|Parameters] section in this topic.
{br}

If you want to delete a detail line during update, you should specify {{true}} as the value of the <tt>delete</tt> property of the corresponding detail entity: {{"delete" : true}}. To identify the detail line to be deleted, you can specify either the values of the key fields of the detail line or the value of the <tt>ID</tt> property.
==HTTP Headers==
You can specify the following headers in the request.[anchor|#_40bf8194-174d-41e1-9ba1-dce56cf597b4]
{| class="checklist" | width="100%" 
|- 
!width="25%" ! Header
!width="75%" ! Description
|- 
| <tt>Accept</tt>
| Specifies the format of the response body, which can be one of the following:[anchor|#_f83ea400-2a04-4b41-a10a-503c0a1e4d35]
*<tt>application/json</tt>
* <tt>text/json</tt>

|- 
|  <tt>Content-Type</tt>
| Specifies the format of the request body, which can be one of the following:[anchor|#_428be305-088a-4941-91fe-3e3183134561]
*<tt>application/json</tt>
* <tt>text/json</tt>

|- 
|  <tt>If-Match</tt>
| Changes the behavior of the {{PUT}} request, which normally either creates a new record or updates an existing one. If you only want to update a record, use the optional <tt>If-Match</tt> header with the {{*}} value.
|}
==Response==
The response of a successful method call contains the updated record in JSON format in the response body. 
==Status Codes==
The following table lists the HTTP status codes that the system returns for a request that updates a record.[anchor|#_970da984-282e-41b1-b56c-841acaa6b024]
{| class="checklist" | width="100%" 
|- 
!width="20%" ! Code
!width="80%" ! Description
|- 
| ''200''
| The request has been completed successfully. The response body contains the updated record.
|- 
| ''400''
| [anchor|#_985e25c7-f5d0-4a85-90cc-91becd791aa1]
The data specified in the request is invalid.
|- 
| ''401''
| [anchor|#_18e114ad-e399-4b02-9094-c28349cbe74f]
The user is not signed in to the system.
|- 
| ''403''
| [anchor|#_aa6cbad4-5523-4d09-9def-73a7c7bc006b]
The user has insufficient rights to access the Acumatica ERP form that corresponds to the entity.
|- 
| ''412''
| You have used the <tt>If-Match</tt> header with the {{*}} value, and the record does not exist.
|- 
| ''429''
| [anchor|#_09fe66fb-52e3-4138-9f89-5a12d4b4982d]
The number of requests has exceeded the limit imposed by the license (see [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_License_Restrictions_API_Users|License Restrictions for API Users]).
|- 
| ''500''
| [anchor|#_f97c2310-d7c1-40b4-a402-c792ebd9aff3]
An internal server error has occurred.
|}
