In Acumatica ERP, some records have attributes that are visible on the '''Attributes''' tab of the data entry form. For details about attributes, see [HelpRoot_Administration\CS__con_Attributes|Attributes]. {br}

You may have to retrieve the records along with their attributes by using the contract-based REST API. To do this, you access the needed URL with the {{GET}} HTTP method, and in the parameters of the request, you specify the desired record fields and the fields that correspond to the needed attributes and attribute values. See the following sections for details on and examples of the URL, parameters, HTTP method, HTTP headers, and response.{br}{TOC}
==URL==
When you retrieve records from Acumatica ERP, you use the following URL.{{{{http://&lt;Base endpoint URL&gt;/&lt;Top-level entity&gt;
}}}}{br}

In this URL:{br}

[anchor|#_9bcc7b7b-b32e-4274-af94-efbd960ba824]
*{{<Base endpoint URL>}} is the URL of the contract-based endpoint through which you are going to work with Acumatica ERP, which has the following format: {{http://<Acumatica ERP instance URL>/entity/<Endpoint name>/<Endpoint version>/}}.
*{{<Top-level entity>}} is the name of the entity for which you are going to retrieve the list of records along with their attributes.
{br}

For example, suppose that you want to retrieve the list of leads along with their attributes from a local Acumatica ERP instance with the name ''AcumaticaDB'', and you want to use the system endpoint with the name ''Default'' and Version 18.200.001. You would use the following URL: ''http://localhost/AcumaticaDB/entity/Default/18.200.001/Lead''.
==Parameters==
When you retrieve records along with their attributes, you should use the following parameters:[anchor|#_87d14a90-4696-4bd3-a205-4a39558ae37c]
*''$select'': To list the desired record fields and the fields that correspond to the needed attributes and attribute values
*''$expand'': To expand the detail entity that contains the fields that correspond to the attributes and attribute values
For example, for the <tt>Lead</tt> entity, to retrieve the values of attributes of records, you need to specify <tt>Attributes/Attribute</tt> and <tt>Attributes/Value</tt> in the ''$select'' parameter, and <tt>Attributes</tt> in the ''$expand'' parameter. To learn the exact names of the fields that correspond to the attributes for a particular entity, you should review the fields of this entity on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_70_60|Web Service Endpoints] ([~/?ScreenId=SM207060|SM207060]) form or refer to the OpenAPI specification of the endpoint.{br}

You can use other parameters as well; see [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_REST_Get_Records|Retrieval of Records by Conditions]. For a detailed description of the ''$select'' and ''$expand'' parameters, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_REST_Parameters|Parameters for Retrieving Records].
==HTTP Method==
You use the {{GET}} HTTP method to retrieve records along with their attributes.
==HTTP Headers==
You can specify the following header in the request.[anchor|#_40bf8194-174d-41e1-9ba1-dce56cf597b4]
{| class="checklist" | width="100%" 
|- 
!width="25%" ! Header
!width="75%" ! Description
|- 
| <tt>Accept</tt>
| Specifies the format of the response body, which can be one of the following:[anchor|#_f83ea400-2a04-4b41-a10a-503c0a1e4d35]
*<tt>application/json</tt>
* <tt>text/json</tt>

|}
