When you need to attach a file to a record by using the contract-based REST API, you access the needed URL address with the {{PUT}} HTTP method and pass the file in the request body. See the following sections for details on the URL, parameters, HTTP method, HTTP header, and response format.{br}{TOC}
==URL ==
If you need to attach a file to a record in Acumatica ERP, you use the following URL.{{{{http://&lt;Base endpoint URL&gt;/&lt;Top-level entity&gt;/&lt;Key value 1&gt;/&lt;Key value 2&gt;/files/&lt;File name&gt;
}}}}
The URL has the following components:[anchor|#_47986599-c001-4f82-b373-342fbda3667a]
*{{<Base endpoint URL>}} is the URL of the contract-based endpoint through which you are going to work with Acumatica ERP, which has the following format: {{http://<Acumatica ERP instance URL>/entity/<Endpoint name>/<Endpoint version>/}}. 
*{{<Top-level entity>}} is the name of the entity to which you are going to attach a file. 
*{{<Key value 1>}} and {{<Key value 2>}} are the values of the key fields of the record to which you are going to attach a file. You use the number and order of key fields as they are defined on the corresponding Acumatica ERP form.
*:((({S:Warn}You can pass the key fields separated by vertical bar (''|'') instead of slash(''/'').
)))
*{{<File name>}} is the name of the file that you are going to attach with the extension.
{br}

For example, suppose that you want to attach the <tt>Sample.jpg</tt> file to the stock item record with inventory ID ''AALEGO500'' in a local Acumatica ERP instance with name ''AcumaticaDB'' by using the system endpoint with the name ''Default'' and Version 18.200.001. You should use the following URL to attach the file: {{http://localhost/AcumaticaDB/entity/Default/18.200.001/StockItem/AALEGO500/files/Sample.jpg}}.
==Parameters==
You use no parameters when you attach a file to a record.
==HTTP Method==
You use the {{PUT}} HTTP method and pass the file to be attached in the request body.
==HTTP Headers==
You can specify the following header in the request.[anchor|#_40bf8194-174d-41e1-9ba1-dce56cf597b4]
{| class="checklist" | width="100%" 
|- 
!width="25%" ! Header
!width="75%" ! Description
|- 
| <tt>Accept</tt>
| Specifies the format of the response body, which can be one of the following:[anchor|#_f83ea400-2a04-4b41-a10a-503c0a1e4d35]
*<tt>application/json</tt>
* <tt>text/json</tt>

|}
==Response==
The response of a successful method call is ''204 No Content''.
==Status Codes==
The following table lists the HTTP status codes that the system returns for a request that attaches a file to a record.[anchor|#_970da984-282e-41b1-b56c-841acaa6b024]
{| class="checklist" | width="100%" 
|- 
!width="20%" ! Code
!width="80%" ! Description
|- 
| ''204''
| The request has been completed successfully. The file is attached. The {{Location}} header of the response contains the URL that you can use to retrieve the file from the system.
|- 
| ''401''
| [anchor|#_f13501df-295b-484e-b841-af2dd664db18]
The user is not signed in to the system.
|- 
| ''403''
| [anchor|#_6f3f423c-8fd2-441f-b8f4-1331d652ddaa]
The user has insufficient rights to access the Acumatica ERP form that corresponds to the entity.
|- 
| ''429''
| [anchor|#_6fedd998-9c04-456d-9fb1-19d23524e73a]
The number of requests has exceeded the limit imposed by the license (see [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_License_Restrictions_API_Users|License Restrictions for API Users]).
|- 
| ''500''
| [anchor|#_9ba700b1-023d-43a7-bf6a-0f98d8bdad84]
An internal server error has occurred.
|}
