GetList() Method (Contract Version 2) This topic describes the  GetList()  method that is available in           Version 2 of the system contract. You use the  GetList()  method to             retrieve from an  Acumatica ERP             data entry form a list of records that satisfy the specified conditions.  Do not                 use the  GetList()  method to retrieve the records from an inquiry                 form; instead, use the  Put()  method. Syntax public Entity[] GetList(Entity entity) Parameter entity : The entity that specifies the             conditions that must be met for the records to be returned from  Acumatica ERP. Return Value The method returns the array of  Entity  objects that correspond to the specified records. Example The following example gets the list of stock items that have the  Active  status and         that were modified within the past month. The code returns all fields of each stock item         record.          //Filter the items by the last modified date and status
StockItem stockItemsToBeFound = new StockItem
