)))A point-of-sale (POS) system can create and process direct sales invoices (that is, invoices for which neither a sales order nor a shipment has been created) and include in these invoices lines for a return of previously sold items. The POS system creates a direct sales invoice and releases the invoice.[anchor|#_2d29a2f1-91cc-47b7-940f-4beca7f47638]((({S:Warn}For simplicity, this example does not include the creation of the payment or the application of the payment to the invoice. You can find an example showing how to create and apply a payment in [HelpRoot_Dev_Integration\IS__con_Entering_Direct_Sales_Invoice|Entry of a Direct Sales Invoice].
